name: Move-On Begins
description: Organizations start moving on to Midway.

name: Construction Begins
description: Organizations start building booths.

name: Blitz Booth Move-On
description: Blitz organizations move to Midway.

name: Final Booth Inspections
description: University Staff (EH&S) arrive for final booth inspections. Direct them to the Head of Booth.

name: Construction Ends
description: Only four members per organization are allowed to remain on their Midway plot.

name: Cleanup Begins
description: Each organization must send two members to the trailer to help cleanup Midway. Direct them to the Head of Booth.

name: Final Fixes Ends
description: All participants must clear off of Midway.

name: Opening Ceromony
description: Speeches, ribbon cutting, and Midway officially opens to the public.

name: Judging Begins
description: Judges arrive on Midway. Direct them to the Co-Chairs or Head of Booth.

name: Night Judging Begins
description: Judges arrive on Midway. Direct them to the Co-Chairs or Head of Booth.

name: Awards Ceromony
description: Organizations may close booths without taking downtime for the Awards Ceromony.

name: Teardown Begins
description: Organizations may begin to teardown booths.

name: Teardown Required Start
description: Organizations must have started teardown.

name: Teardown Ends
description: All organizations must be clear of Midway.

name: Quiet Hours Start
description: No loud noise on Midway. If you can hear something outside a booth, it is too loud. Close the shipping container.

name: Take out trailer trash
description: Pick up all loose trash in the trailer, put it in a trash bag, tie up the trash bag, and put the trash near the door. When the watch shift checks in have them put the trash in a dumpster before they move the dumpsters.
